  "prompt": "How do I build endurance for rowing? I can row about 2 km and then start failing.",
  "response": "To build endurance for rowing, try these strategies:\n\n1. Gradual progression\n- Slowly increase distance and time\n- Add 500m to your distance each week\n- Rest between intervals to recover\n\n2. Interval training\n- Mix high-intensity and low-intensity rowing\n- Example: 500m hard, 500m easy\n- Gradually reduce rest time between intervals\n\n3. Strength training\n- Focus on core, back, and leg exercises\n- Squats, deadlifts, and planks\n- Helps improve overall rowing performance\n\n4. Cardiovascular conditioning\n- Running, cycling, swimming\n- Cross-training helps build overall endurance\n\n5. Technique improvement\n- Proper form reduces energy expenditure\n- Take rowing technique classes\n- Watch instructional videos\n\n6. Consistent practice\n- Row 3-4 times per week\n- Gradually increase intensity and duration\n\n7. Nutrition and recovery\n- Eat balanced diet with adequate protein\n- Stay hydrated\n- Get enough sleep\n- Allow muscle recovery time\n\n8. Mental training\n- Practice visualization\n- Set realistic goals\n- Stay motivated and consistent\n\nRemember to listen to your body and progress gradually to avoid injury.",
